<subSubSection pageId="3" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,1554,2084]" pageId="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,318,1554,1580]" pageId="3">Etymology</emphasis>
:—The epithet is dedicated to Dr.Armando Jesús Urquiola Cruz (1949–2009), eminent Cuban botanist, founder of the Botanical Garden of Pinar de Río, who dedicated his life to the study and conservation of the flora of Pinar de Río, the 
<taxonomicName box="[327,445,1626,1652]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="3" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Myrtaceae</taxonomicName>
family and Cuban aquatic plants. Professor Urquiola was the first to recognize this species as new to science, in an expedition with the first author in 2007.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,1554,2084]" pageId="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,481,1697,1724]" pageId="3">Distribution and habitat</emphasis>
:—Local endemic species of Sierra de Nipe. It is only known from the Charrascales de La Caridad, near the Naranjo river (
<geoCoordinate box="[537,688,1733,1760]" degrees="20.474592" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="3" precision="1" value="20.474592">20.474592 N</geoCoordinate>
; - 
<geoCoordinate box="[708,865,1733,1760]" degrees="75.740322" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="3" precision="1" value="-75.74032">75.740322 W</geoCoordinate>
), Mayarí municipality, 
<collectingRegion box="[1127,1324,1734,1760]" country="Cuba" name="Holguin" pageId="3">Holguín province</collectingRegion>
(
<figureCitation box="[1339,1437,1734,1760]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[136,229,1449,1471]" captionTargetBox="[177,1415,405,1414]" captionTargetId="figure-108@3.[151,1436,389,1424]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Geographical location of the Myrcia urquiolae population in Holguín (eastern Cuba), La Mensura-Piloto National Park, near the Naranjo river, in the charrascales of La Caridad." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6605256" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6605256/files/figure.png" pageId="3">Figure 3</figureCitation>
). It grows in xeromorphic sub-thorny thickets over serpentinite rocks, on ferromagnesian red-brownish fersialitic soils, between 
<quantity box="[237,365,1805,1832]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.75" metricValueMax="4.5" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="3" unit="m" value="375.0" valueMax="450.0" valueMin="300.0">300–450 m</quantity>
elev. The shrub strata of the charrascal, where the species lives, varies between 
<quantity box="[1272,1344,1806,1832]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="3" unit="m" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3–4 m</quantity>
in height and its cover on the ground is 70–80%. Species composition include 
<taxonomicName authority="(Standley 1918: 42) Delprete (1999: 221)" authorityName="Delprete" authorityPageNumber="221" authorityYear="1999" baseAuthorityName="Standley" baseAuthorityPageNumber="42" baseAuthorityYear="1918" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Mazaea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="3" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="shaferi">
<emphasis box="[934,1110,1842,1868]" italics="true" pageId="3">Mazaea shaferi</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Standley, P. C." box="[1126,1337,1842,1868]" pageId="3" pagination="3 - 86" refId="ref3168" refString="Standley, P. C. (1918) Rubiaceae. North American Flora 32 (1): 3 - 86." type="journal article" year="1918">Standley 1918: 42</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation author="Delprete, P. G." pageId="3" pagination="217 - 230" refId="ref2438" refString="Delprete, P. G. (1999) The Cuban endemic genera Ariadne, Mazaea, Acunaeanthus, Phyllomelia (Rondeletieae), and Eosanthe (Rubiaceae). Brittonia 51 (2): 217 - 230. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 2666631" type="journal article" year="1999">Delprete (1999: 221)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Grisebach 1866: 67) Engler (1883: 367)" authorityName="Engler" authorityPageNumber="367" authorityYear="1883" baseAuthorityName="Grisebach" baseAuthorityPageNumber="67" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[283,975,1877,1904]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Anacardiaceae" genus="Metopium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="3" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="venosum">
