</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Britton (1915: 505)" authorityName="Britton" authorityPageNumber="505" authorityYear="1915" box="[997,1429,1913,1940]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Plumeria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="3" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nipensis">
<emphasis box="[997,1201,1914,1940]" italics="true" pageId="3">Plumeria nipensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Britton, N. L." box="[1209,1429,1913,1940]" pageId="3" pagination="487 - 517" refId="ref2199" refString="Britton, N. L. (1915) Studies of West Indian plants - VII. Bulletin of the Torrey Botanical Club 42: 487 - 517. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 2479726" type="journal article" year="1915">Britton (1915: 505)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
y 
<taxonomicName authority="(Grisebach 1866: 125) Borhidi (2002: 227)" authorityName="Borhidi" authorityPageNumber="227" authorityYear="2002" baseAuthorityName="Grisebach" baseAuthorityPageNumber="125" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[136,876,1949,1976]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Solenandra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="3" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="myrtifolia">
<emphasis box="[136,382,1950,1976]" italics="true" pageId="3">Solenandra myrtifolia</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Grisebach, A." box="[397,633,1949,1976]" pageId="3" refId="ref2767" refString="Grisebach, A. (1866) Catalogus plantarum cubensium exhibens collectionem Wrightianam aliasque minores ex insula Cuba missas. Leipzig. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 177" type="book" year="1866">Grisebach 1866: 125</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation author="Borhidi, A." box="[649,876,1950,1976]" pageId="3" pagination="223 - 231" refId="ref2166" refString="Borhidi, A. (2002) Revalidacion del genero Solenandra Hook. f. (Rubiaceae). Acta Botanica Hungarica 44 (3 - 4): 223 - 231." type="journal article" year="2002">Borhidi (2002: 227)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,1554,2084]" pageId="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,455,1985,2011]" pageId="3">Reproductive biology</emphasis>
:—Tiny yellowish-white flowers with numerous stamens indicate probable insect pollination. Although the fruits of the new species are unknown, dispersal by birds has been reported for other 
<taxonomicName pageId="3">
<emphasis box="[1372,1452,2022,2047]" italics="true" pageId="3">Myrcia</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Torezan-Silingardi, H. M. &amp; Alves, P. E. A. M." box="[231,610,2058,2084]" pageId="3" pagination="23 - 43" refId="ref3254" refString="Torezan-Silingardi, H. M. &amp; Alves, P. E. A. M. (2004) Phenology and reproductive ecology of Myrcia rostrata and M. tomentosa (Myrtaceae) in Central Brazil. Phyton 44 (1): 23 - 43." type="journal article" year="2004">Torezan-Silingardi &amp; Alves 2004</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,158,760]" pageId="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,427,158,184]" pageId="4">Conservation status</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Z. Acosta" authorityYear="2022" box="[463,659,158,184]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Myrcia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="4" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="urquiolae">
<emphasis box="[463,659,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="4">Myrcia urquiolae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known from only one locality, which was affected by fire in 
<date pageId="4" value="2019-03">March 2019</date>
. In the only population known to date, 
<specimenCount box="[617,706,194,221]" pageId="4" type="adult">25 adult</specimenCount>
individuals have been registered in an extent of occurrence and area of occupation of 
<quantity box="[324,380,230,256]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="4" unit="km" value="1.0">1 km</quantity>
<superScript attach="left" box="[380,388,230,244]" fontSize="6" pageId="4">2</superScript>
. Although this locality is located within La Mensura-Piloto National Park, a managed protected area of national significance, this site is vulnerable to increased fire frequency. For this reason, a future decrease in the area, extent and quality of habitat and in the number of mature individuals is projected. Therefore, according to 
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN" box="[136,286,338,364]" pageId="4" refId="ref2803" refString="IUCN (2019) Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 14. Prepared by the Standards and Petitions Subcommittee. Available from: http: // www. iucnredlist. org / documents / RedListGuidelines. pdf (accessed 22 December 2021)." type="book" year="2019">IUCN (2019)</bibRefCitation>
criteria, the available data support the evaluation of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Z. Acosta" authorityYear="2022" box="[871,1065,338,364]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Myrcia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="4" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="urquiolae">
<emphasis box="[871,1065,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="4">Myrcia urquiolae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as Critically Endangered (CR), by criteria: B1ab(ii, iii,v)+2ab(ii, iii,v); C2a(i,ii); D.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,158,760]" pageId="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,428,410,436]" pageId="4">Taxonomic remarks</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Z. Acosta" authorityYear="2022" box="[464,659,410,436]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Myrcia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="4" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="urquiolae">
<emphasis box="[464,659,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="4">Myrcia urquiolae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to 
<taxonomicName authority="sect. Myrcia" box="[788,1012,411,437]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Myrcia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="4" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Myrcia">
<emphasis box="[788,868,411,436]" italics="true" pageId="4">Myrcia</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis box="[932,1012,411,436]" italics="true" pageId="4">Myrcia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
due to its hairy floral disc and the nonprolonged hypanthium on the summit of the ovary, characters that distinguish it from the other sections of the genus. Additionally, it presents a thickened staminal ring, which comprises more than 50% of the disc (vs. less than 30% in 
<taxonomicName box="[167,436,518,545]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Myrcia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="4" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Gomidesia">
<emphasis box="[167,247,519,544]" italics="true" pageId="4">Myrcia</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis box="[315,436,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="4">Gomidesia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(O. 
<bibRefCitation author="Berg, O." box="[491,610,518,545]" pageId="4" pagination="1 - 472" refId="ref2146" refString="Berg, O. (1855 - 1856) Revisio Myrtacearum Americae. Linnaea 27: 1 - 472." type="journal article" year="1855">Berg 1855</bibRefCitation>
–1856: 5) B. S. Amorim &amp; E. Lucas in 
<bibRefCitation author="Lucas, E. J. &amp; Amorim, B. S. &amp; Lima, D. F. &amp; Lourenco, A. R. L. &amp; NicLughadha, E. M. &amp; Proenca, C. E. B. &amp; Rosa, P. O. &amp; Rosario, A. S. &amp; Santos, L. L. &amp; Santos, M. F. &amp; Souza, M. C. &amp; Staggemeier, V. G. &amp; Vasconcelos, T. N. C. &amp; Sobral, M." box="[1067,1298,518,545]" pageId="4" pagination="1 - 12" refId="ref3022" refString="Lucas, E. J., Amorim, B. S., Lima, D. F., Lourenco, A. R. L., NicLughadha, E. M., Proenca, C. E. B., Rosa, P. O., Rosario, A. S., Santos, L. L., Santos, M. F., Souza, M. C., Staggemeier, V. G., Vasconcelos, T. N. C. &amp; Sobral, M. (2018) A new infra-generic classification of the species-rich Neotropical genus Myrcia s. l. Kew Bulletin 73 (9): 1 - 12. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / S 12225 - 017 - 9730 - 5" type="journal article" year="2018">
Lucas 
<emphasis box="[1142,1201,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="4">et al.</emphasis>
2018: 9
</bibRefCitation>
), and anthers with thecae of equal size that open completely in two equal parts (vs. vertically displaced that retain curvature at dehiscence) (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Lucas, E. J. &amp; Amorim, B. S. &amp; Lima, D. F. &amp; Lourenco, A. R. L. &amp; NicLughadha, E. M. &amp; Proenca, C. E. B. &amp; Rosa, P. O. &amp; Rosario, A. S. &amp; Santos, L. L. &amp; Santos, M. F. &amp; Souza, M. C. &amp; Staggemeier, V. G. &amp; Vasconcelos, T. N. C. &amp; Sobral, M." box="[328,526,590,617]" pageId="4" pagination="1 - 12" refId="ref3022" refString="Lucas, E. J., Amorim, B. S., Lima, D. F., Lourenco, A. R. L., NicLughadha, E. M., Proenca, C. E. B., Rosa, P. O., Rosario, A. S., Santos, L. L., Santos, M. F., Souza, M. C., Staggemeier, V. G., Vasconcelos, T. N. C. &amp; Sobral, M. (2018) A new infra-generic classification of the species-rich Neotropical genus Myrcia s. l. Kew Bulletin 73 (9): 1 - 12. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / S 12225 - 017 - 9730 - 5" type="journal article" year="2018">
Lucas 
<emphasis box="[402,451,590,616]" italics="true" pageId="4">et al</emphasis>
. 2018
</bibRefCitation>
). The phylogenetic position of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Z. Acosta" authorityYear="2022" box="[874,1020,590,616]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Myrcia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="4" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="urquiolae">
<emphasis box="[874,1020,590,616]" italics="true" pageId="4">M. urquiolae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<taxonomicName authority="sect. Myrcia" box="[1056,1281,591,617]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Myrcia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="4" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Myrcia">
<emphasis box="[1056,1136,591,616]" italics="true" pageId="4">Myrcia</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis box="[1201,1281,591,616]" italics="true" pageId="4">Myrcia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was proven by 
<bibRefCitation author="Flickinger, J. A. &amp; Jestrow, B. &amp; Oviedo, R. &amp; Santiago-Valentin, E. &amp; Sustache-Sustache, J. &amp; Jimenez-Rodriguez, F. &amp; Campbell, K. C. St. E. &amp; Francisco-Ortega, J." box="[136,390,626,653]" pageId="4" pagination="448 - 480" refId="ref2505" refString="Flickinger, J. A., Jestrow, B., Oviedo, R., Santiago-Valentin, E., Sustache-Sustache, J., Jimenez-Rodriguez, F., Campbell, K. C. St. E. &amp; Francisco-Ortega, J. (2020) A phylogenetic survey of Myrtaceae in the Greater Antilles with nomenclatural changes for some endemic species. Taxon 69 (3): 448 - 480. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / tax. 12263" type="journal article" year="2020">
Flickinger 
<emphasis box="[258,308,626,652]" italics="true" pageId="4">et al</emphasis>
. (2020
</bibRefCitation>
, as 
<taxonomicName box="[432,572,626,653]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Myrcia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="4" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undefined-1">
<emphasis box="[432,512,627,652]" italics="true" pageId="4">Myrcia</emphasis>
sp. 1
</taxonomicName>
), where in the phylogeny of the family for the Greater Antilles it nested along with 
<taxonomicName authority="Urban (1923: 87)" authorityName="Urban" authorityPageNumber="87" authorityYear="1923" box="[192,563,662,688]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Myrcia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="4" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="apodocarpa">
<emphasis box="[192,363,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="4">M. apodocarpa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Urban, I." box="[369,563,662,688]" pageId="4" pagination="55 - 176" refId="ref3302" refString="Urban, I. (1923) Plantae cubenses novae vel rariores a clo. Er. L. Ekman lectae. I. In: Urban, I. (Ed.) Symbolae antillanae 9. Leipzig, pp. 55 - 176." type="book chapter" year="1923">Urban (1923: 87)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(C. Wright 1869: 433) Urban (1923: 86)" authorityName="Urban" authorityPageNumber="86" authorityYear="1923" baseAuthorityName="C. Wright" baseAuthorityPageNumber="433" baseAuthorityYear="1869" box="[574,1157,662,689]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Myrcia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="4" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="retivenia">
<emphasis box="[574,709,663,688]" italics="true" pageId="4">M. retivenia</emphasis>
(C. 
<bibRefCitation author="Wright, C." box="[754,951,662,688]" pageId="4" pagination="428 - 436" refId="ref3383" refString="Wright, C. (1869) Flora cubana. Anales de la Academia de Ciencias Medicas, Fisicas y Naturales de la Habana, Revista Cientifica 5: 428 - 436." type="journal article" year="1869">Wright 1869: 433</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation author="Urban, I." box="[965,1157,662,689]" pageId="4" pagination="55 - 176" refId="ref3302" refString="Urban, I. (1923) Plantae cubenses novae vel rariores a clo. Er. L. Ekman lectae. I. In: Urban, I. (Ed.) Symbolae antillanae 9. Leipzig, pp. 55 - 176." type="book chapter" year="1923">Urban (1923: 86)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Urban 1925: 341) Alain (1971: 138)" authorityName="Alain" authorityPageNumber="138" authorityYear="1971" baseAuthorityName="Urban" baseAuthorityPageNumber="341" baseAuthorityYear="1925" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Myrcia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="4" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="abbottiana">
<emphasis box="[1209,1366,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="4">M. abbottiana</emphasis>
(Urban 1925: 341) 
<bibRefCitation author="Alain &amp; Bro" box="[264,469,698,724]" pageId="4" pagination="107 - 157" refId="ref2118" refString="Alain, Bro. (1971) Novitates antillanae. IV. Memoirs of the New York Botanical Garden 21 (2): 107 - 157." type="journal article" year="1971">Alain (1971: 138)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Regarding the other species of the section in 
<collectingCountry box="[985,1047,698,724]" name="Cuba" pageId="4">Cuba</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Z. Acosta" authorityYear="2022" box="[1058,1204,698,724]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Myrcia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="4" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="urquiolae">
<emphasis box="[1058,1204,698,724]" italics="true" pageId="4">M. urquiolae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs by its strongly revolute linear leaves.
</paragraph>
